element.name: Carysfort Cache by Team OLK, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)
element.description: A nice little cache in Blackrock, Co Dublin.
element.long-description:
This cache is located in a nice park hidden off Carysfort Ave. Parking can be found at these coordinates: N 53 17.616 W 006 11.122.
The park used to be the gardens and farm of Carysfort Convent and Teacher Training College. The nuns sold the land and the buildings have been used for the Smurfitt Business School.
The cache is in a small tupperware container.
element.encoded-hints: Yew know you are there when yew are at the one nearest the little hedges.

Found this one while visiting my little brother who lives about 8 metres away.... TFTC TNLN

2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by Simotaniously
Great little cache I live very near by so brought the dogs for a walk in the park. It took me a few mins but found it. Very well hidden.

2010-04-21T19:00:00Z : Found it by Fitzet
An enjoyable lunchtime break.
Lovely park, good weather & a straightforward find, using the hint.
TNLN SL TFTC

2008-10-11T19:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
At first we were barking up the wrong tree, but soon corrected that and the cache was in hand shortly afterwards. Nice snug spot for it.
